Detailed Description

BSP Utility functions header file This file declares the functions required to create, add and remove nodes. Also provides various memset functions.

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum BspUtils_LinkAddMode

Enums for the different modes of adding a node to a link list.

struct BspUtils_LinkAddMode

Enumerator
BSPUTILS_LAM_TOP 

Add nodes to the top of the list.

BSPUTILS_LAM_BOTTOM 

Add nodes to the bottom of the list.

BSPUTILS_LAM_PRIORITY 

Add nodes to the list based on ascending order of priority. Nodes with the same priority are always added to the bottom of the existing nodes with same priority.

enum BspUtils_LinkListType

Enums for the type of link list to be created.

struct BspUtils_LinkListType

Enumerator
BSPUTILS_LLT_DOUBLE 

Double link list.

BSPUTILS_LLT_CIRCULAR 

Circular link list using double link list.

enum BspUtils_NodDir

Enums for the different modes of adding a node to a link list.

struct BspUtils_LinkAddMode

Enumerator
BSPUTILS_NODE_DIR_HEAD 

Add nodes to the top of the list.

BSPUTILS_NODE_DIR_TAIL 

Add nodes to the bottom of the list.

void BspUtils_linkNodePri ( BspUtils_Handle  handle,
BspUtils_Node *  node,
UInt32  priority 
)

Links a node to the linked list according to the list type The memory to the node object should be allocated by the caller. This is used for link list with priority.

BspUtils_linkNodePri

Parameters
handleLink list handle.
nodeNode object pointer used for linking.
priorityPriority of the node used for priority based addition of nodes. Priority is in descending order the value. So 0 is the highest priority and is added to the top of the node. Nodes with the same priority are always added to the bottom of the existing nodes with same priority. For non-priority based modes, this parameter is ignored and could be set to 0.

Int32 BspUtils_linkUniqePriNode ( BspUtils_Handle  handle,
BspUtils_Node *  node,
UInt32  priority 
)

Very similar to BspUtils_linkNode, except that on equal priority nodes will not be inserted. An error (BSP_EBADARGS) would be returned. Applicable for double linked list only. ToDo Update to handle circular list also.

BspUtils_linkUniqePriNode

Parameters
handleLink list handle.
nodeNode object pointer used for linking.
priorityPriority of the node used for priority based addition of nodes. Priority is in descending order the value. So 0 is the highest priority and is added to the top of the node. Nodes with the same priority are always added to the bottom of the existing nodes with same priority. For non-priority based modes, this parameter is ignored and could be set to 0.
